<p><strong>The Pachakuti Mesa Tradition</strong> is a system that utilizes an altar like arrangement called a mesaÂ at its coreÂ yet emphasizes the flexibility, the cultural context, and the creative potential of each apprentice in a way <strong>that transforms not only their lives, but also the planet.</strong></p>

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_4"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Ritual Arts" url_new_window="off" use_icon="off" icon_color="#7EBEC5" use_circle="off" circle_color="#7EBEC5" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#7EBEC5" image="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ceremony-180.jpg" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid" url="http://heartofthehealer.org/shamanic-ritual-arts/"]

<p>Through the study and practice of shamanic ritual arts, individuals learn to <strong>live in harmony with nature and Mother Earth</strong> and her children, the animal, plants, minerals and each other.</p>

